hconres34-118:
To express disapproval of the withdrawal by the Secretary of the Interior of approximately 225,504 acres of National Forest System lands in Cook, Lake, and Saint Louis Counties, Minnesota, from disposition under the United States mineral and geothermal leasing laws.

Whereas, on February 25, 2023, the Secretary of the Interior withdrew approximately 225,504 acres of National Forest System lands in Cook, Lake, and Saint Louis Counties, Minnesota, from disposition under the United States mineral and geothermal leasing laws;

Whereas, the withdrawal of these lands from mineral and geothermal leasing would prevent the development of critical minerals and energy resources that are essential to the United States economy and national security;

Whereas, the withdrawal of these lands would also prevent the creation of jobs and economic development in Minnesota and the surrounding region;

Now, therefore, be it resolved by the Senate and House of Representatives of the United States of America in Congress assembled,

Section 1. Disapproval of withdrawal.

The withdrawal of approximately 225,504 acres of National Forest System lands in Cook, Lake, and Saint Louis Counties, Minnesota, from disposition under the United States mineral and geothermal leasing laws is hereby disapproved.

Sec. 2. Authorization of appropriations.

There are authorized to be appropriated such sums as may be necessary to carry out this resolution.
